M|references|1. Click "Preview" in GTM
M|references|2. Enter site URL
M|references|3. GTM debug panel opens at bottom
M|references|**What to check:**
M|references|- Tags fired on this event
M|references|- Tags not fired (and why)
M|references|- Variables and their values
M|references|- Data layer contents
M|references|**Tag not firing:**
M|references|- Check trigger conditions
M|references|- Verify data layer push
M|references|- Check tag sequencing
M|references|**Wrong variable value:**
M|references|- Check data layer structure
M|references|- Verify variable path (nested objects)
M|references|- Check timing (data may not exist yet)
M|references|**Multiple firings:**
M|references|- Check trigger uniqueness
M|references|- Look for duplicate tags
M|references|- Check tag firing options
M|references|Use workspaces for team collaboration:
M|references|- Default workspace for prd
M|references|- Separate workspaces for large changes
M|references|- Merge when ready
M|references|**Best practices:**
M|references|- Name every version descriptively
M|references|- Add notes explaining changes
M|references|- rv changes before publish
M|references|- Keep prd version noted
M|references|**Version notes example:**
M|references|```
M|references|v15: Added purchase conversion tracking
M|references|- New tag: GA4 - Event - Purchase
M|references|- New trigger: Custom Event - purchase
M|references|- New variables: DL - transaction_id, DL - value
M|references|- Tested: Chrome, Safari, Mobile
M|references|```
M|references|```javascript
M|references|// Default state (before consent)
M|references|gtag('consent', 'default', {
M|references|'analytics_storage': 'denied',
M|references|'ad_storage': 'denied'
M|references|});
M|references|// Update on consent
M|references|function grantConsent() {
M|references|gtag('consent', 'update', {
M|references|'analytics_storage': 'granted',
M|references|'ad_storage': 'granted'
M|references|});
M|references|}
M|references|```
M|references|1. Enable Consent Overview in Admin
M|references|2. Configure consent for each tag
M|references|3. Tags respect consent state automatically
M|references|**Setup tags to fire in order:**
M|references|Tag cfg > Advanced Settings > Tag Sequencing
M|references|**Use cases:**
M|references|- Config tag before event tags
M|references|- Pixel initialization before tracking
M|references|- Cleanup after conversion
M|references|**Trigger exceptions** - Prevent tag from firing:
M|references|- Exclude certain pages
M|references|- Exclude internal traffic
M|references|- Exclude during testing
